	<title>Simulating a Program</title>

	<p>Once a program is ready to be simulated, press the <gui style="button">Run</gui> button on the toolbar, choose
		<guiseq><gui style="menu">Program</gui><gui style="menuitem">Run</gui></guiseq> or press <key>F5</key>.</p>
	<p>The program will step through at the <gui style="input">Clock speed</gui> set in the simulation panel, with the currently executing
		instruction being emboldened in the editing area and its opcode in memory also being emboldened. Hardware outputs in the hardware panel
		and simulation displays in the simulation panel will be updated as the program executes.</p>
	<p>While the program is running, most of the <app>MCUS</app> interface will be disabled. To pause the program and allow controls to be
		used, press the <gui style="button">Pause</gui> button on the toolbar, choose
		<guiseq><gui style="menu">Program</gui><gui style="menuitem">Pause</gui></guiseq> or press <key>F6</key>.</p>
	<p>When paused, the program can also be stepped-through, instruction by instruction, to see exactly how execute proceeds and affects the
		simulated hardware. To do this, press <gui style="button">Step Forward</gui> on the toolbar, choose
		<guiseq><gui style="menu">Program</gui><gui style="menuitem">Step Forward</gui></guiseq> or press <key>F8</key>.</p>
	<p>To stop simulation of the program at any time, press <gui style="button">Stop</gui> on the toolbar, choose
		<guiseq><gui style="menu">Program</gui><gui style="menuitem">Stop</gui></guiseq> or press <key>F7</key>.</p>

	<note style="tip">
		<p>If demonstrating a simulation to a large audience, it can be useful to fullscreen <app>MCUS</app>. This can be achieved by clicking the
			<gui style="button">Fullscreen</gui> button on the toolbar, selecting
			<guiseq><gui style="menu">Edit</gui><gui style="menuitem">Fullscreen</gui></guiseq> or pressing <key>F11</key>. In fullscreen mode,
			the main window is maximised and the font size of key parts of the interface is increased to improve visibility.</p>
		<p>To leave fullscreen mode, press <key>F11</key> again, or click the <gui style="button">Leave Fullscreen</gui> button on the toolbar.</p>
	</note>
